<p>Oakland's Mediterranean climate is characterized by dry summers and mild, wet winters, making it ideal for high-efficiency heat pump systems. For most Oakland homes, a heat pump with a SEER rating of 16-20 and an HSPF of 9-10 provides optimal year-round comfort while minimizing energy consumption. The moderate temperature swings mean that systems rarely work at maximum capacity, extending equipment life and improving efficiency.</p>

